axiom.tool.rock.meld_strength.descriptio:
How strongly the tool melds together with the ground
This is affected by the 'Smoothing StdDev'
axiom.tool.rock.noisiness.description:
How strongly blocks are influenced by the noise field
0 = no noise, spherical
1 = strong noise, blobs
axiom.tool.rock.smoothing_stddev.descrip:
0 = no smoothing
2 = normal (~4 blocks) smoothing
5 = very strong (~10 blocks) smoothing

axiom.tutorial.active_block: Some tools require a block to paint with or place. Here you can switch blocks by clicking on the icon
axiom.tutorial.box_select_tool1:
This is the Box Select Tool.
It selects blocks between two points
axiom.tutorial.box_select_tool2:
To start using the tool, click one point, drag your mouse to another point and then release.
Afterwards, you can adjust with the Gizmos.
To confirm the selection, press Enter
axiom.tutorial.clipboard: This is your clipboard. If you have a selection you can copy blocks to here using Ctrl+C. Afterwards you can use Ctrl+V to initiate a placement
axiom.tutorial.history: Axiom keeps track of block changes so you can undo and redo, this window shows those changes. (Tip: left-click rewinds history, right-click looks at the change)
axiom.tutorial.magic_select_tool:
This is the Magic Select Tool.
It select adjacent blocks of the same type
axiom.tutorial.main_window:
This is the main viewport.
%s to rotate the camera.
%s to use tools.
%s to use the arcball camera.
Scroll to quickly move towards/away from a point
axiom.tutorial.sculpt_draw_tool:
This is the Sculpt Draw Tool.
It allows you to sculpt terrain, pulling blocks based on the surface normal
axiom.tutorial.selection1:
This is a selection.
Selections allow you to apply tools and operations to specific parts of the world.
To clear a selection, press Enter
axiom.tutorial.selection2:
%s can be used to fill the selection with blocks.
%s allows you to replace blocks.
%s/%s/Delete to copy/cut/delete
axiom.tutorial.slope_tool1:
This is the Slope Tool.
It allows you to slope terrain between two points
axiom.tutorial.slope_tool2: To use the tool, click once to set the target position. Then, move your mouse to a different position and click+drag to draw a slope between the two points
axiom.tutorial.tool_options: Here you can find the settings for your selected tool
axiom.tutorial.tools_window: This is the Tools Window. Here you can select tools for painting, terraforming, making selections and more
axiom.creative_search_quick_add: Press Enter to quick-add first block
